   The information and forms available through the links below are
   provided by the Philadelphia Department of Revenue. All questions or
   comments concerning these forms should be directed to the Department of
   Revenue at (215) 686-6569; E-mail address: revenue@phila.gov.  CHECK
   BACK OFTEN TO OBTAIN  CURRENT PHILADELPHIA TAX INFORMATION.  To visit
   the City of Philadelphia home page (phila.gov), click here.

   WHAT'S NEW :
   Highlights current important information.

   TAX GUIDE:
   Provides an overview of Philadelphia taxes and tax information.
   Summary listing of taxes and tax rates.

   TAX FORMS:
   Go here to download City of Philadelphia tax returns, applications,
   forms, instructions and coupons.
   State Tax Forms-http://www.revenue.state.pa.us/
   Federal Tax Forms-http://www.irs.ustreas.gov
   All tax forms on this site are in Adobe Acrobat Format. In order to
   download the forms, you will need Adobe Acrobat version 4.0 or higher.
   Adobe Acrobat is available free of charge. (Note that some of these
   forms and publications are large and will take several minutes to
   download.)
   To Download Adobe Acrobat

   TAXPAYER REGISTRATION:
   Go here for an application for a business tax account or an individual
   earnings tax account.  The business tax account number will be assigned
   by the Department.  The earnings tax number is your social security
   number.

   ELECTRONIC FILING:
   Highlights the programs that enable Business Privilege, Net Profits,
   School Income and Wage Reconciliation Tax returns to be filed
   electronically.

   TECHNICAL RULINGS:
   Get a synopsis of court decisions and departmental rulings on various
   tax topics.

   FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS/TAX FILING TIPS:
   Review the most frequently asked questions and their answers.  Get a
   list of tax filing tips that should help alleviate common mistakes.

   The City of Philadelphia intends to provide this site as a service to
   its citizens but in no way makes any warranties about the fitness or
   the accuracy of any of the content maintained on phila.gov or its
   links. The City of Philadelphia further assumes no liability for
   anything that could go wrong if you use these pages including, but not
   limited to, computer crashes or late fees/ penalties associated with
   reliance on this information.

